dct_description_sm: View drawn by Mr. G.F. McDougall Mast. R.N. ; Engraved by E. Radclyffe ; Engraved by J. & C. Walker ; Sold by J.D. Potter Agent for the Admiralty Charts.
Depths shown by soundings, relief by hachures and heights (rising from coasts).
Magnetic Variation in 1900, increasing about 3' to 4' annually.
Shows low water areas, coasts, villages, anchorages.
[Inset chart]: Entrance to the White Sea
